<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="650" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[131,776,1302,1432]" pageId="7" pageNumber="650">ETYMOLOGY. — This fossil is unusual in its three-dimensional preservation, which allows distinguishing not only the structure of the mesosoma in great detail, but also reveals paired bulges present on T3-T5. It owes its name to these little hills on the metasoma.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
